      <sentence>
         <text>Growing crops for food matters to the US.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>In 1870, 70-80 percent of the workers in the US were in farming.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
		 <text>Today, it is just 2-3 percent.</text>
		 <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		 <text>Farmers have become better at getting more food from the same amount of land.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
    </sentence>
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
    <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
    </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>The main job on a farm is to grow and raise food for the US.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
		  <text>They grow many things from corn and salad crops to peanuts.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>They also have many dairy and beef cattle, and pigs.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Children used to work on farms where they lived.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>      
      <sentence>
         <text>Not many of them do that now.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
	   <sentence>
		 <text>There are laws in place to make sure that children who live on farms come to no harm.</text>
		 <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	   </sentence>
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
